The Woolworths and Coles chain stores in Australia, on Saturday and Sunday evening, lowered the purchase limit for toilet paper in all stores nationwide to two and one pack per purchase respectively.
ALDI store also announced on Monday a one-package purchase limit.
The restrictions were announced in the form of messages on the boxes and on the Facebook page of the chain stores.
