Unlike previous measures, these restrictions were enforceable by the police and by issuing fines and dispersing gatherings.
A closure order was issued for most businesses, except for businesses that were considered "essential" including supermarkets, pharmacies, banks, hardware stores, gas stations and construction sites.
On January 20, the first known case of COVID-19 in the Pacific Northwest region of Washington State was confirmed to be a man who had returned from Wuhan on January 15.
