Three vaccination strategies are currently under investigation.
First, researchers are perfectly capable of creating a viral vaccine.
The use of a virus, inactivated or dead, is aimed at preventing the development of an immune reaction in the human body to a new COVID-19 infection.
A second strategy, single-subunit vaccines, is being pursued, with the goal of developing a vaccine that can make the immune system more susceptible to certain subunits of the virus.
In the case of SARS-CoV-2, this research is based on the S-spike protein that helps the virus to enter the ACE2 enzyme receptor.
A third strategy is linked to nucleic acid vaccines (DNA or RNA vaccines, a novel method of vaccine preparation).
